                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/1396: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-12-06T18:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 6—1 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>217. Following is text of Foreign Office statement issued today: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The detailed agreement regarding the Shantung railway was signed at
                            Peking on December 5th at 6 p.m., the amount of compensation for the
                            railway being fixed at 40,000,000 yen and the rate of interest at 6 per
                            cent per annum. Under this agreement it has been decided that the
                            transfer of the railway shall begin at noon, January 1st, 1923, to be
                            completed within a month. This latest agreement marks the completion of
                            all the necessary arrangements regarding the restitution of
                            Shantung.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
